benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/catalog/priceList - Retrieve priceList for a given subscription and date

covered: Valid Request flows: TC01–TC04 cover successful retrieval with various param combos, returning HTTP 200 and a PriceList JSON object.
Authorization: TC08 covers unauthorized access handling (HTTP 401).
Empty data handling: TC13 covers empty dataset responses (HTTP 404 or default).
Comprehensive query parameter coverage: Tests TC01, TC02, TC03, TC04, TC11, TC12, TC19 validate handling of various parameter combinations, sizes, and extra parameters.

Error and edge cases: TC05 (invalid subscriptionId), TC07 (invalid date format), TC06 (non-existent subscription), TC21 (date boundary regression), TC22 (XSS), TC10 (SQL injection) cover input validation and security risks.
Service reliability and performance: TC09 (service unavailable), TC20 (dependent service unavailable), TC14/TC15 (response times), TC17 (retry behavior), TC18 (large data volume).
Security tests: TC10, TC22 cover injection and XSS scenarios.
Backward compatibility and accessibility: TC16 (legacy clients) and TC23 (screen reader accessibility).
gaps: Pagination: No tests for paging large priceList results.
Caching behavior: No tests for caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) and cache invalidation.
Rate limiting: No tests for throttling or 429 responses under bursts.
403 forbidden coverage: Only 401 tested; add test for insufficient permissions resulting in 403.
Internal server error: No tests simulating 500 errors; only 502/503 tests.
UI integration considerations: Additional tests to simulate UI rendering or end-user UI behavior could be explored.
recommendations: Add explicit pagination tests to validate page navigation for large priceList results (page size, total count, navigation links).
Add caching header tests (ETag, Cache-Control) and validation of cache invalidation behavior.
Add rate-limiting tests (simulate bursts) and 429 responses; include concurrency testing.
Extend error coverage to include 403 Forbidden and 500 Internal Server Error scenarios; ensure no internal details leak in error responses.
Consider parameterized tests to efficiently cover multiple date/subscription combinations and ensure deterministic test data setup.
If UI is involved, expand accessibility tests beyond screen readers to include keyboard navigation and ARIA labeling.
